---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Retrogaze — Ray Weiss"
  description="Retrogaze. AI-powered pixel art generator for eight retro consoles, validated against real hardware constraints."
>
  <main class="px-6 py-24 lg:px-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1
        class="font-sans text-4xl font-medium tracking-tight text-foreground lg:text-5xl"
      >
        Retrogaze
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 font-serif text-lg text-muted">
        AI-powered pixel art generator for eight retro consoles. Sprites and
        tilesets validated against real hardware constraints.
      </p>

      <div class="prose-body mt-16">
        <p>
          The differentiation is not "looks retro." Retrogaze enforces the
          real hardware constraints of each target console: NES gets 54
          colors with four per tile, Game Boy gets four shades, Genesis gets
          512 colors. Output is genuinely playable on real hardware and
          faithful emulators.
        </p>
        <p>
          Supported platforms: NES, Game Boy (DMG, Pocket, Color), Commodore
          64, Genesis, SNES, and PC-Engine. Target audience: indie devs,
          game jam participants, pixel artists, retro modders.
        </p>

        <h2>Try it</h2>

        <p>
          Live at <a href="https://retrogazeai.com">retrogazeai.com</a>
          (closed beta).
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
